# What Docker must NOT copy into the build.
#
# Everything here is either useless in the image, harmful in it, or just slow
# to send. Docker copies the whole project folder ("build context") to the
# daemon before it runs a single instruction, so an unignored .venv or
# node_modules costs a gigabyte on every build.

# --- Harmful: host-built, platform-specific ---
# The venv is compiled for macOS/arm64. Inside a Linux container it is not
# just dead weight (~1.1 GB, torch alone is 533 MB) — if it shadowed the
# container's own site-packages the app would fail in confusing ways.
backend/.venv/
backend/venv/
**/node_modules/

# --- Secrets: never bake credentials into an image layer ---
# Image layers are readable by anyone who pulls the image. Config arrives at
# *run* time via compose env_file, never at build time.
.env
**/.env
!.env.example

# --- Local state: the container makes its own ---
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
backend/helix.db

# --- Build output: stage 1 rebuilds this from source ---
frontend/app/dist/
frontend/dist/

# --- Dev-only: the baton says keep e2e and Playwright out of the image ---
frontend/app/e2e/
**/.pytest_cache/
**/__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
**/.mypy_cache/
**/.ruff_cache/

# --- Version control & CI ---
.git/
.github/
.gitignore

# --- Editor / OS noise ---
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store

# --- Documentation & coursework: none of it runs ---
# ~12 MB of reports, zips and design mockups. Kept in the repo on purpose,
# but there is no reason to ship them inside a running server.
*.md
!README.md
*.docx
*.pdf
*.zip
UIUX design request/
Helix-LaTeX/
docs/
demo_artifacts/
*.html
read.txt
